President Trump delivered remarks in the Grand Foyer of the White House, where he highlighted the benefits of the recently agreed-upon tax legislation. He emphasized that the tax cuts will provide relief for American families and businesses, and will lead to job creation and economic growth. The President mentioned several families who will benefit from the tax cuts, sharing specific examples of how their tax bills will be reduced. He also stated that the IRS has confirmed that Americans will see lower taxes and bigger paychecks beginning in February if Congress passes the bill before Christmas. President Trump expressed his belief that tax cuts are an American principle, not a partisan issue, and emphasized his goal of creating an economy where every American can experience the dignity of work and the satisfaction of a job well done. He urged the public to support the tax cuts and help bring about a brighter future for America.